  "prompt": "Do people judge you?",
  "response": "Yes, people can and do judge others based on a variety of factors such as appearance, behavior, opinions, and social status. Judgments can be conscious or unconscious and may be influenced by personal experiences, cultural norms, and societal expectations. It's a natural part of human interaction, but it's worth remembering that everyone has their own perspectives and biases, and judgments may not always be fair or accurate. Ultimately, focusing on self-awareness and understanding can help navigate such judgments.",
